A People’s Democratic Party (PDP) presidential aspirant and former Senate President, Abubakar Bukola Saraki has unveiled his agenda for the country, promising to take tough decisions for Nigeria to survive. Speaking during a breakfast party with the media and friends, the former Kwara State governor said he knows how business works, how government functions and how the legislature operates. “This diverse experience stands me out. And I will bring the experience to bear in getting the most critical constituencies behind the tough decisions that we must take if Nigeria must survive.”